<br>
Umbagollah is an imaginary country founded by The Gov in November 1999. Shortly after its foundation, its first citizen (Co Whatsinaname) joined, who was also founder of Cuyuni Republica Isles, a very weird kind of nation. Maybe a website of it stille exists these days. Other people soon followed, and roleplaying became a popular activity. The first big story played both in Cuyuni and Umbagollah and ended in a marriage with double suicide. This story was turned into a musical by Samara Jalaya, after our founder the oldest active citizen.<br>
<br>
People joined and people left, as happens in every country. A big chance occurred with a sudden burst of activity by a citizen who called himself Mindspring. Under the name of Komordus<br>
(at first nobody knew they were the same) he invaded Umbagollah with an army of lords and daemons. While doing so, Komordus, an experienced rolpelayer, brought roleplaying to a new level. He set<br>
the current roleplaying standards and introduced some common RP laws. This first invasion lead to a second invasion, spies and the loss of bagpipers in the woods, we kept ourselves occupied with it for about half a year. Another major improvement in this time was the change to the ezboard forum, which was more suitable for long and varied discussions than the bravenet forum that had been used before.<br>
<br>
In january 2001, The Gov made a post at micro-nations.org with the question whether Umbagollah was a micronation or not. I have never seen the discussion, but I think the outcome was that Umbagollah a micronation, but a different one. Anyhow, Umbagollah was immediately recognised by Babkhan protectorate of Bathland and the Cordial Kingdom of Kelterspruf. This had several consequences: it lead to more relations<br>
between Umbagollah and the microworld (mostly through me. Note, however, that Umbagollah was not a complete<br>
stranger to micronations: it had long ties with Cuyuni, and it was part of the webring of imaginary countries.)Secondly, it lead to the arrival of Thomas Mountian of Bathland in Umbagollah. After a few weeks Thomas and Samara started the storyworld of Roquatirrihn, which slowly evolved into a real life drama that lasted for more than a year. Those who were around at that time know, all others don't have to. <br>
In 2001 another very active citizen (at the time) joined, Casandra Fireblade. Most roleplaying threads that lived (sort of) until beginning this year, were still a direct or indirect result of her coming to Umbagollah. In 2002 the things have quieted down a bit, but the board activity cycle in Umbagollah is more or less the same as on all other boards (high activity in Autumn and Spring, low activity in Summer and Winter).<br>
<br>
Note that I did not say &quot;micronation&quot; in the beginning but &quot;imaginary country&quot;. The history of Umbagollah as a country is marked by the quest for its identity: it is a micronation, but without a government simulation. Umbagollah has a government structure, but only in its fictional (roleplaying) part. It is a roleplaying world, but without magic: magic spells are unstable in the Umbagollan air. The keywords for Umbagollah are originality and creativity. That is also a reason for the anti-magic law: you have to use your imagination to solve a tough situation instead of simply do some hocus-pocus to solve it. Umbagollah is a project to build a world that is possible, but still distinctively different. Musicals have been crafted, and stories. Animals and plants were created, sports, subcultures, infrastructure. The history of Umbagollah is also marked by the constant threat to slip into inactivity. The reason that it hasn't happened yet is that a small group of its current inhabitants know each other for such a long time now that they have become quite close friends. There are always a few of us who have enough time to keep the board alive. <br>
<br>
